<TITLE> Exercise 'Shanti Doot-2' takes off Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 31 (bdnews24.com)The peace support operations exercise, styled "Exercise Shanti Doot-2", is set to start on April 1, an official statement said Monday. The Bangladesh Army and the United States Pacific Command (USPACOM) are the host and co-sponsor of the exercise, the Inter-Service Public Relations Directorate said. The exercise consists of two packagescommand post exercise (CPX), slated for April 1-11 at Radisson, and field training exercise (FTX) scheduled for April 1-20 at Bangladesh Institute of Peace Support Operation Training (BIPSOT) at Rajendrapur Cantonment. The exercise will continue until April 20 under the Global Peace Operations Initiative Programme framework. Around 360 military personnel from 11 countries will participate in the FTX. About 120 military and civil personnel from 16 countriesAustralia, Bangladesh, Brunei, Cambodia, Canada, India, Indonesia, Nepal, the Philippines, Singapore, Sri Lanka, South Korea, UK, Mongolia, Tonga and the US will join the CPX. Bangladesh holds 25 key appointments including exercise director/UN Force Headquarters commander and force commander in the CPX. Exercise director/UN Force Headquarters commander is brigadier general Md Rafiqul Islam and exercise force commander is brigadier general Mohammad Mahboob Haider Khan. The CPX will have three segments such as academic session on April 1-4, mini exercise on April 5 and exercise play on April 7-11. The certificate awarding ceremony of the CPX will be held at Radisson on April 11, to be attended by the naval chief, vice admiral Sarwar Jahan Nizam. bd
